data.value:
Heidelberg is an intimate city built around southwestern Germany, divided into two by the Neckar River and reminiscent of the postcard beauty. The historic extension of the city, which is 15 minutes away from Mannheim, dates back to the Roman Empire.
As the oldest university in Germany, Heidelberg University is rising in the center of the mountainous city. The Palace, the German Pharmacy Museum, the Botanical Garden, the Haus zum Ritter, the house of Friedrich Ebert and the Kurpfälzisches Museum are some of the important works that give the touristic charm to the region.
